dcterms:description: The HEXACO personality inventory is a 6-dimensional model of personality, measuring the facets honesty-humility, emotionality, extraversion, agreeableness, conscientiousness, and openness to experience.

dcterms:description: The Human Values Scale measures ten universal values grouped into four categories: self-transcendence, conservation, self-enhancement, and openness-to-change through self-reports.
dcterms:title: Human Values Scale (HVS)

dcterms:description: The Alternative Uses Test is a standard measure to assess human creativity by asking participants to devise creative uses for everyday objects.

dcterms:description: The Cognitive Reflection Test is designed to measure the tendency to override an incorrect 'gut' response and engage in further reflection to find the correct answer.
